Welcome to the Tutorial! 

This will mostly show off the controls on how this game works.

Mario here will mostly act like SMW but may be different when playing here.
Be aware about this if you're used to MW Physic

bash note

this area is not finish and very wip lol.

also tiles are WIP... hopefully

- Jumping -
You can jump by pressing Z. The more you hold Z, the higher you can go!
Most basic stuff ever I know...

- Running -
By holding X. Mario will start to run! The more you move without stopping at all the faster you will run!

- Running -
When running at Max-Speed. Your jump will increase when holding Z. Use this to reach higher platforms

Blocks - Rotating
When hit. These blocks will rotate for a certain amount of time. On which you can go through them.

Blocks - Rotating
Some rotating blocks may includes items like Coins, Mushrooms etc...

- Spin Jump -
When big. You can destroy rotating blocks below you if empty by pressing C to start a Spin Jump.

- Checkpoints -
Collecting these will save your last location if you die. You also become big if interacting while as Small Mario!

- Item Reserve -
Collecting a mushroom for example while Big will reverse it. Pressing the Space button will drop said item

- Yoshi Coins -
These special coins appears on most level. Collecting all 5 in a level will give you a extra life!

What? You though a pit in the tutorial will kill you? Nope!

Just take this pipe to return to the surface

- Switch Blocks -
When not activated. These blocks won't be solid. However activing a switch block will!

- Springs -
Useful to reach hard to jump spots. Hold Z to reach higher places!

- Springs -
Remember that not all springs can be picked up... Keep that in mind.

By holding X on items like Springs or Keys. Mario will be holding said item.
